				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">To clarify, koitsu means before the start of rendering, which begins at the end of the vertical blank. Vertical blank starts at the beginning of NMI, and lasts for a short period of time, during which you need to make all needed writes to $2007, then write to $2005 twice to set your scroll position.<br /><br />If all of this is not done before your reach the end of the vertical blank, you will have visual problems, i.e. some of the $2007 writes will go to unexpected addresses (nametable corruption), and the scroll will be wrong.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
